sdp/logs/Lead_T-054a_1779567517.log:3802:tric computation and threshold reporting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 3 total:** ~36 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -65,15 +60,15 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 29 | T-029 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-001 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 30 | T-030 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-002 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 31 | T-031 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-003 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 32 | T-032 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-004 | T-001 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 33 | T-033 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-005 | T-001 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 34 | T-034 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-006 | T-001 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 35 | T-035 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-007 | T-001 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 36 | T-036 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-008 | T-001 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 37 | T-037 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-009 | T-001 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 24 | T-024 | Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-001 | T-001 | - `sample_library.SampleRecord` defined with fields: `sample_id` (UUID), `path` (Path), `source` (Literal['library','self','room','contact','theramini','keyboard']), `character_tags` (frozenset[str]), `pitch_hz` (float &#124; None), `pitch_confidence` (float), `duration_sec` (float), `captured_at` (datetime), `arc_phase` (str &#124; None), `mood` (dict[str,float] &#124; None), `presence` (Literal['present','none','unknown'] &#124; None), `rms` (float), `peak` (float), `transient_density` (float), `gain_db` (float, default 0.0)<br/>- dataclass is frozen and JSON-serializable; ISO-8601 timestamp round-trip<br/>- tests verify schema, defaults, JSON round-trip, and rejection of out-of-range values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 25 | T-025 | Define controlled `CHARACTER_TAGS` vocabulary (warm, metallic, wind, pulse, voice, mechanical, water, sustained, transient, percussive, harmonic, noisy). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-002 | T-001 | - `sample_library.CHARACTER_TAGS` is a frozenset of exactly the 12 listed tags<br/>- `SampleRecord.character_tags` validation rejects unknown tags<br/>- tests verify rejection path and the canonical 12-tag set |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 26 | T-026 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-003 | T-001 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=,